I am not sure this is doable at 33, as it has been a very very long time since I was 33 (and spent most of that time in CT and CC).  But be that as it may...<br>
<br>
I liked soloing the Evil Eyes in Beholder's Maze.  They drop coin, gems and two very sellable items.  They are enchanters so keep resist magic up.  As for tactics, I have no idea at 33 as I can 1 shot them.  Maybe invis to spot, get pet, buff, nuke, get nuked, pet adds, mezz its pet (if up).  As I recall they are on a 6 minute timer, so its pretty quick.  Various mudmen and minotaurs are there as well (Minos drop horns and mino axes - very sellable 3 years ago doubt it today).<br>
<br>
Also, one (and I know you could do this) could solo the Wisps in Erudins Crossing.  Greater Lightstones net about 9pp per drop.  If you can manage it, the guards at the hole in the wall in Misty Thicket drop 10pp of stuff per kill.<br>
